# Chaos Test 3: Disconnect the Queue (RabbitMQ)
# Date: 2026-04-17

=== 1. BASELINE: Trigger a sensor update, confirm alert pipeline works ===
{"id":"sensor-001","name":"Living Room Thermostat","type":"temperature","location":"living_room","value":85,"unit":"fahrenheit","status":"active","last_reading":"2026-04-17T15:59:17Z","created_at":"2026-04-13T04:38:36Z","updated_at":"2026-04-17T15:59:17Z"}
HTTP 200

--- Alert metrics before outage ---
# HELP events_received_total Total sensor.updated events consumed from RabbitMQ.
# TYPE events_received_total counter
events_received_total 2
# HELP events_processed_total Total events that completed evaluation.
# TYPE events_processed_total counter
events_processed_total 2
# HELP alerts_triggered_total Total alerts triggered by threshold crossings.
# TYPE alerts_triggered_total counter
alerts_triggered_total 3

=== 2. FAILURE INJECTED: Stop RabbitMQ ===
a4-rabbitmq-1

=== 3. DURING OUTAGE: Sensor update ===
HTTP write still succeeds (Postgres is independent); publish fails.
{"id":"sensor-001","name":"Living Room Thermostat","type":"temperature","location":"living_room","value":99,"unit":"fahrenheit","status":"active","last_reading":"2026-04-17T15:59:23Z","created_at":"2026-04-13T04:38:36Z","updated_at":"2026-04-17T15:59:23Z"}
HTTP 200

